  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the top 10 inspirational movies of the 21st century?",
  "response": "Here are ten inspirational movies from the 21st century that have resonated with audiences and critics alike:\n\n1. **The Pursuit of Happyness (2006)** - Based on a true story, this film starring Will Smith follows Chris Gardner's struggle with homelessness while trying to secure a better life for himself and his son.\n\n2. **Slumdog Millionaire (2008)** - This film tells the story of a young man from the slums of Mumbai who becomes a contestant on a game show. His journey illustrates themes of love, fate, and perseverance.\n\n3. **127 Hours (2010)** - Based on the true story of Aron Ralston, who becomes trapped by a boulder in a remote canyon, this film showcases the human will to survive against all odds.\n\n4. **The Blind Side (2009)** - This biographical sports drama tells the story of Michael Oher, a homeless African American teen who becomes an All-American football player with the help of a caring woman and her family.\n\n5. **Coach Carter (2005)** - Based on the true story of a high school basketball coach who prioritizes education over athletics, this film emphasizes the importance of discipline, teamwork, and academic success.\n\n6. **A Beautiful Mind (2001)** - This biographical drama chronicles the life of mathematician John Nash, who struggles with schizophrenia but ultimately achieves great success and received the Nobel Prize in Economics.\n\n7. **Hidden Figures (2016)** - This inspiring story highlights the contributions of three African American women at NASA during the space race, showcasing their intelligence, perseverance, and impact on history.\n\n8. **Life of Pi (2012)** - This visually stunning adaptation of the novel tells the tale of a young boy stranded on a lifeboat with a Bengal tiger, exploring themes of faith, survival, and resilience.\n\n9. **The Help (2011)** - Set in the 1960s, this film tells the story of African American maids working in white households and their fight for dignity and respect, illustrating the power of storytelling and friendship.\n\n10. **Wonder (2017)** - Based on the novel by R.J. Palacio, this heartwarming story follows a boy with facial differences as he navigates school and teaches those around him about kindness and acceptance.\n\nThese films inspire through their powerful narratives, character development, and themes of perseverance, hope, and resilience.",
